enemy_1220_dzoms.ability: <@eb.key>Reborn Creation</> (takes <@eb.key>greatly reduced</> Physical and Arts damage); Units blocking it gain <@eb.key>+1 Block</> (up to a maximum of +6).

enemy_1220_dzoms_2.name: Touch of Benevolence
enemy_1220_dzoms_2.description: One of the Sanguinarch of Vampires' more elaborate creations, flexible and difficult to defeat. According to rumors, the Sanguinarch is able to snatch the blood of other creatures, imbuing new life into it and taking it under his control. Those given new life should praise the Sanguinarch for his benevolence.
enemy_1220_dzoms_2.ability: <@eb.key>Reborn Creation</> (takes <@eb.key>greatly reduced</> Physical and Arts damage); Units blocking it gain <@eb.key>+1 Block</> (up to a maximum of +6).

enemy_1221_dzomg.name: Gift of the Sanguinarch
enemy_1221_dzomg.description: A creation of the Sanguinarch of Vampires' Originium Arts that bears greater vitality. One who was powerful in life will continue to be a great threat to their enemies even after being reshaped by the power of the Sanguinarch's blessing.
enemy_1221_dzomg.ability: <@eb.key>Reborn Creation</> (takes <@eb.key>greatly reduced</> Physical and Arts damage); Units blocking it gain <@eb.key>+1 Block</> (up to a maximum of +6).

enemy_1221_dzomg_2.name: Gift of Magnanimity
enemy_1221_dzomg_2.description: A creation of the Sanguinarch of Vampires' Originium Arts that bears exceptional vitality. One who was powerful in life will continue to be a great threat to their enemies even after being reshaped by the power of the Sanguinarch's blessing. Therefore, those who continue ought to thank the Sanguinarch for his magnanimity.
enemy_1221_dzomg_2.ability: <@eb.key>Reborn Creation</> (takes <@eb.key>greatly reduced</> Physical and Arts damage); Units blocking it gain <@eb.key>+1 Block</> (up to a maximum of +6).

enemy_1222_dpvt.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Warrior
enemy_1222_dpvt.description: A warrior of the Sarkaz Royal Court blessed with the living blood of the Sanguinarch of Vampires. After falling in battle for the first time, his blood will continue to advance in his place.
enemy_1222_dpvt.ability: Will be reborn as a <@eb.key><Touch of the Sanguinarch></> after falling in battle for the first time.

enemy_1222_dpvt_2.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Warrior Captain
enemy_1222_dpvt_2.description: A captain of the Sarkaz Royal Court blessed with the living blood of the Sanguinarch of Vampires, more dangerous than a normal Sarkaz Royal Court Soldier. After falling in battle for the first time, his blood will continue to advance in his place.
enemy_1222_dpvt_2.ability: Will be reborn as a <@eb.key><Touch of Benevolence></> after falling in battle for the first time.

enemy_1223_dmech.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Artificer
enemy_1223_dmech.description: An artificer of the Sarkaz Royal Court blessed with the living blood of the Sanguinarch of Vampires. They gained a portion of Victoria's engineering expertise and are responsible for operating the reloading system of Londinium's city defense artillery.
enemy_1223_dmech.ability: Continuously charges up <@eb.key>Londinium Secondary Defense Artillery</>; when interrupted, the Defense Artillery will <@eb.key>lose a portion</> of its charge progress. Will be reborn as a <@eb.key><Touch of the Sanguinarch></> after falling in battle for the first time.

enemy_1223_dmech_2.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Artificer Captain
enemy_1223_dmech_2.description: An artificer captain of the Sarkaz Royal Court blessed with the living blood of the Sanguinarch of Vampires. They gained a great amount of Victoria's engineering expertise and are responsible for operating the reloading system of Londinium's city defense artillery.
enemy_1223_dmech_2.ability: Continuously charges up <@eb.key>Londinium Secondary Defense Artillery</>; when interrupted, the Defense Artillery will <@eb.key>lose a portion</> of its charge progress. Will be reborn as a <@eb.key><Touch of Benevolence></> after falling in battle for the first time.

enemy_1224_dsuply.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer ASV
enemy_1224_dsuply.description: An armored supply vehicle blessed by the Sanguinarch of Vampires. While on the battlefield, enhances Gift of the Sanguinarch and Touch of the Sanguinarch.
enemy_1224_dsuply.ability: While in battle, reborn creations have <@eb.key>increased ATK</>, and their attacks will additionally deal <$ba.dt.apoptosis>Necrosis damage</>.

enemy_1224_dsuply_2.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Retrofit ASV
enemy_1224_dsuply_2.description: An armored supply vehicle meticulously blessed by the Sanguinarch of Vampires. While on the battlefield, enhances Gift of the Sanguinarch and Touch of the Sanguinarch.
enemy_1224_dsuply_2.ability: While in battle, reborn creations have <@eb.key>increased ATK</>, and their attacks will additionally deal <$ba.dt.apoptosis>Necrosis damage</>.

enemy_1225_dkmage.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Chain Caster
enemy_1225_dkmage.description: A caster of the Sarkaz Royal Court blessed by the Sanguinarch of Vampires. Trained by the Royal Court, they pose a wide-ranging threat on the battlefield with their Arts.
enemy_1225_dkmage.ability: Attacks deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</> and <$ba.dt.apoptosis>Necrosis damage</> and jump between 4 targets, with each jump dealing reduced damage. Will be reborn as a <@eb.key><Gift of the Sanguinarch></> after falling in battle for the first time.

enemy_1225_dkmage_2.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Chain Caster Captain
enemy_1225_dkmage_2.description: A caster captain of the Sarkaz Royal Court blessed by the Sanguinarch of Vampires, more experienced than a normal Caster. Trained by the Royal Court, they pose a wide-ranging threat on the battlefield with their Arts.
enemy_1225_dkmage_2.ability: Attacks deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</> and <$ba.dt.apoptosis>Necrosis damage</> and jump between 4 targets, with each jump dealing reduced damage. Will be reborn as a <@eb.key><Gift of Magnanimity></> after falling in battle for the first time.

enemy_1226_dklord.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Hatedrinker
enemy_1226_dklord.description: A soldier of the Sarkaz Royal Court blessed by the Sanguinarch of Vampires. The hatred of their compatriots slain on the battlefield builds up within them, making them more than eager to tear apart the enemies of the Sarkaz.
enemy_1226_dklord.ability: Gains <@eb.key>increased ATK</> for each reborn creation on the battlefield; Will be reborn as a <@eb.key><Gift of the Sanguinarch></> after falling in battle for the first time.

enemy_1226_dklord_2.name: Sarkaz Heirbearer Wrathgorger
enemy_1226_dklord_2.description: An elite soldier of the Sarkaz Royal Court blessed by the Sanguinarch of Vampires. The wrath of their compatriots slain on the battlefield builds up within them, making them more than eager to tear apart every last enemy of the Sarkaz.
enemy_1226_dklord_2.ability: Gains <@eb.key>increased ATK</> for each reborn creation on the battlefield; Will be reborn as a <@eb.key><Gift of Magnanimity></> after falling in battle for the first time.

enemy_1227_dair.name: Sarkaz Requisitioned Engineering Drone
enemy_1227_dair.description: An engineering drone requisitioned by the Sarkaz Royal Court. They are a part of Londinium's defense system, modified to be more stealthy, but at the cost of greater wear-and-tear.
enemy_1227_dair.ability: <$ba.invisible>Invisible</>, and gradually loses HP over time. Charges up <@eb.key>Londinium Secondary Defense Artillery</> when attacking.

enemy_1227_dair_2.name: Sarkaz Requisitioned Cutting-Edge Drone
enemy_1227_dair_2.description: A more sophisticated engineering drone requisitioned by the Sarkaz Royal Court. They are a part of Londinium's defense system, modified to be more stealthy, but at the cost of greater wear-and-tear.
enemy_1227_dair_2.ability: <$ba.invisible>Invisible</>, and gradually loses HP over time. Charges up <@eb.key>Londinium Secondary Defense Artillery</> when attacking.

enemy_1228_dslime.name: Bloodthirsty Heir
enemy_1228_dslime.description: A creation of the Sanguinarch of Vampires' Originium Arts. They always thirst for more blood, strengthening themselves by stealing the blood of others.
enemy_1228_dslime.ability: Attacks deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</>, and restore HP proportional to damage dealt.

enemy_1228_dslime_2.name: Engorged Heir
enemy_1228_dslime_2.description: A creation of the Sanguinarch of Vampires' Originium Arts. Though their bodies are already engorged with the blood of others, their thirst never ceases.
enemy_1228_dslime_2.ability: Attacks deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</>, and restore HP proportional to damage dealt.

enemy_1229_darmy.name: Sarkaz Royal Court Soldier
enemy_1229_darmy.description: A soldier of the Sarkaz Royal Court. Londinium's munitions factories work day and night to produce weapons for the Sarkaz war effort. They boast a distinctly Sarkaz fighting style, but with greater discipline.

enemy_1229_darmy_2.name: Sarkaz Royal Court Elite Soldier
enemy_1229_darmy_2.description: An elite soldier of the Sarkaz Royal Court. Under Manfred's training, they are not only more formidable warriors, but also more professional.

enemy_1230_dsbudr.name: Nethersea Founder
enemy_1230_dsbudr.description: A Sea Terror that has inexplicably grown a chitinous skull. There is no corresponding organ to be found beneath it.
enemy_1230_dsbudr.ability: Spawns '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' at its location when defeated; Increased RES.

enemy_1230_dsbudr_2.name: Nourished Founder
enemy_1230_dsbudr_2.description: A Sea Terror that generally only metamorphoses within an abundance of the nethersea brand. They can on exceptionally rare occasions be born from the remains of their multiple kin.
enemy_1230_dsbudr_2.ability: Spawns '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' at its location when defeated; Increased RES.

enemy_1230_dsbudr_4.name: Regressed Founder
enemy_1230_dsbudr_4.description: A special individual among the Founders. Heeding the call of We Many, its body is ready to be preyed upon.
enemy_1230_dsbudr_4.ability: Spawns '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' and leaves behind <@eb.key>Remains</> at its location when defeated; [Directed Evolution] Increased RES.

enemy_1231_dsrunr.name: Nethersea Predator
enemy_1231_dsrunr.description: A Sea Terror that has learned to use its chitinous skull to deal physical attacks, storing scraps of food in its body comprised of countless tiny creatures.
enemy_1231_dsrunr.ability: Cannot be blocked while on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>'; Gains Physical and Arts dodge (disabled by certain negative statuses).

enemy_1231_dsrunr_2.name: Nourished Predator
enemy_1231_dsrunr_2.description: A Sea Terror that has learned to hunt efficiently. They themselves do not appear to require nutrients, instead reserving them for their lower-level kin. Before they die, they turn themselves into one last food source.
enemy_1231_dsrunr_2.ability: Cannot be blocked while on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>'; Gains Physical and Arts dodge (disabled by certain negative statuses).

enemy_1231_dsrunr_4.name: Regressed Predator
enemy_1231_dsrunr_4.description: A special individual among the Predators. Heeding the call of We Many, its body is ready to be preyed upon.
enemy_1231_dsrunr_4.ability: Cannot be blocked while on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' and leaves behind <@eb.key>Remains</> at its location when defeated; [Directed Evolution] Gains Physical and Arts dodge (disabled by certain <$ba.debuff>negative statuses</>).

enemy_1232_dssalr.name: Nethersea Brandguider
enemy_1232_dssalr.description: A new type of Sea Terror formed from a colony that was about to decay and die. In order to effectively utilize the last bit of nutrients in their bodies, all they need to do is smear themselves across the ground.
enemy_1232_dssalr.ability: After falling below half HP, spreads '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' to tiles it travels over and gains increased DEF and Block requirement.

enemy_1232_dssalr_2.name: Nourished Brandguider
enemy_1232_dssalr_2.description: Even if not on the verge of death, they will still choose to expand the survival range of their kin using their own flesh and blood. Reminiscent of the Bishop's final journey back to Iberia.
enemy_1232_dssalr_2.ability: After falling below half HP, spreads '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' to tiles it travels over and gains increased DEF and Block requirement.

enemy_1232_dssalr_4.name: Regressed Brandguider
enemy_1232_dssalr_4.description: A special individual among the Brandguiders. Heeding the call of We Many, its body is ready to be preyed upon.
enemy_1232_dssalr_4.ability: After falling below half HP, spreads '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' to tiles it travels over; leaves behind <@eb.key>Remains</> at its location when defeated. [Directed Evolution] Gains increased DEF and Block requirement.

enemy_1233_dsshtr.name: Nethersea Spewer
enemy_1233_dsshtr.description: Possesses a hard, chitinous shell that it uses to protect itself, possibly capable of sporulation or a similar function. A commonly seen Sea Terror where the nethersea brand proliferates.
enemy_1233_dsshtr.ability: Can attack all targets located on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>'; Attacks up to 3 targets at once.

enemy_1233_dsshtr_2.name: Nourished Spewer
enemy_1233_dsshtr_2.description: A Sea Terror that has largely lost control of its functions, spewing out its spore-like progeny at a rate that surpasses its physical capacity, causing it to wear itself out prematurely.
enemy_1233_dsshtr_2.ability: Can attack all targets located on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>'; Attacks up to 3 targets at once.

enemy_1233_dsshtr_4.name: Regressed Spewer
enemy_1233_dsshtr_4.description: A special individual among the Spewers. Heeding the call of We Many, its body is ready to be preyed upon.
enemy_1233_dsshtr_4.ability: Can attack all targets located on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' and leaves behind <@eb.key>Remains</> at its location when defeated; [Directed Evolution] Attacks up to 3 targets at once.

enemy_1234_dsubrl.name: Nethersea Swarmcaller
enemy_1234_dsubrl.description: A rare Sea Terror, able to manipulate the tiny creatures in the air and on the ground to eat away at their surroundings even in the absence of the nethersea brand. They seem to call the brand itself to life, hence their name.
enemy_1234_dsubrl.ability: Continually inflicts <@eb.key>Arts damage</> and <@eb.key>Nervous Impairment</> in an area around it; Has <@eb.key>status resistance</> and is immune to <$ba.sluggish>Slow</>.

enemy_1234_dsubrl_2.name: Nourished Swarmcaller
enemy_1234_dsubrl_2.description: A special and extremely-rare individual, boasting incredible destructive power and far-reaching transmission range. They are unable to be dealt with through conventional means, Inquisitors must be extra vigilant around them.
enemy_1234_dsubrl_2.ability: Continually inflicts <@eb.key>Arts damage</> and <@eb.key>Nervous Impairment</> in an area around it; Has <@eb.key>status resistance</> and is immune to <$ba.sluggish>Slow</>.

enemy_1234_dsubrl_4.name: Regressed Swarmcaller
enemy_1234_dsubrl_4.description: A special individual among the Swarmcallers. Heeding the call of We Many, its body is ready to be preyed upon.
enemy_1234_dsubrl_4.ability: Continually inflicts <@eb.key>Arts damage</> and <@eb.key>Nervous Impairment</> in an area around it; leaves behind <@eb.key>Remains</> at its location when defeated; [Directed Evolution] Has <@eb.key>status resistance</> and is immune to <$ba.sluggish>Slow</>.

enemy_1235_dsbskr.name: Nethersea Reefbreaker
enemy_1235_dsbskr.description: An extremely aggressive individual born from the nethersea brand, capable of inflicting tremendous damage to its surrounding environment for its kin to transform. Lifeforms not considered kin fall under this category.
enemy_1235_dsbskr.ability: <$ba.invisible>Invisible</> while located on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>'; Gains increased ATK for each time it deals damage, decaying quickly after it stops attacking.

enemy_1235_dsbskr_2.name: Nourished Reefbreaker
enemy_1235_dsbskr_2.description: A Sea Terror born from the nethersea brand, used to expel entities that pose a significant threat to its kin, or to completely destroy environments unsuitable for sustaining life. All civilizations on land fall under this category.
enemy_1235_dsbskr_2.ability: <$ba.invisible>Invisible</> while located on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>'; Gains increased ATK for each time it deals damage, decaying quickly after it stops attacking.

enemy_1235_dsbskr_4.name: Regressed Reefbreaker
enemy_1235_dsbskr_4.description: A special individual among the Reefbreakers. Heeding the call of We Many, its body is ready to be preyed upon.
enemy_1235_dsbskr_4.ability: <$ba.invisible>Invisible</> while located on '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>'; leaves behind <@eb.key>Remains</> at its location when defeated; [Directed Evolution] Gains increased ATK for each time it deals damage, decaying quickly after it stops attacking.

enemy_1238_ltmob.name: 'Street Layabout'
enemy_1238_ltmob.description: Armed militants disguised as Infected, they are well-acquainted with the local situation. They look no different from ordinary Infected and easily blend into the crowd.
enemy_1238_ltmob.ability: When attacking targets outside of Realigned Flux, deals a certain percentage of <@eb.key>Arts damage</>

enemy_1238_ltmob_2.name: 'Street Drunk'
enemy_1238_ltmob_2.description: Armed militants disguised as Infected, they are overly acquainted with the local situation, to the point that they have become alcoholics hanging around the street pubs, their mission long forgotten.
enemy_1238_ltmob_2.ability: When attacking targets outside of Realigned Flux, deals a certain percentage of <@eb.key>Arts damage</>

enemy_1239_ltbow.name: 'Street Performer'
enemy_1239_ltbow.description: Armed militants disguised as Infected, they know the local situation by heart. Their weapon of choice is the triangle simply because it is easy to carry around, and definitely not because the triangle has no grade certification and is easy to play.
enemy_1239_ltbow.ability: When attacking targets outside of Realigned Flux, <@eb.key>deals an additional hit</>

enemy_1239_ltbow_2.name: 'Street Musician'
enemy_1239_ltbow_2.description: Armed militants disguised as Infected, they are overly acquainted with the local situation. Aware that they may be exposed by their unfamiliarity with other instruments, they choose to use the triangle.
enemy_1239_ltbow_2.ability: When attacking targets outside of Realigned Flux, <@eb.key>deals an additional hit</>

enemy_1240_ltgint.name: Mass-Produced Colossus
enemy_1240_ltgint.description: An Originium Arts creation that sacrifices stability for miniaturization. Well-equipped for breaching, it is often used to break through enemy lines. Like its creator, it is vulnerable to interference from external energy.
enemy_1240_ltgint.ability: Can only be blocked by Operators with <@eb.key>2 Block or higher</>; When in Realigned Flux, DEF and RES are greatly reduced

enemy_1240_ltgint_2.name: Enhanced Mass-Produced Colossus
enemy_1240_ltgint_2.description: An Originium Arts creation that sacrifices stability for miniaturization. Very well-equipped for breaching, it is often used to break through enemy lines. Its physical strength has been improved but its weakness to interference remains an issue.
enemy_1240_ltgint_2.ability: Can only be blocked by Operators with <@eb.key>2 Block or higher</>; When in Realigned Flux, DEF and RES are greatly reduced

enemy_1241_ltmage.name: Spire Caster
enemy_1241_ltmage.description: One of the backbones of the Leithanian army. Able to cause large area damage under relatively stable conditions. Absent support equipment and personnel, they are vulnerable to interference from external energy.
enemy_1241_ltmage.ability: Attacks 2 targets at once; When attacking targets outside of Realigned Flux, deals <@eb.key>splash damage</>

enemy_1241_ltmage_2.name: Battleworn Spire Caster
enemy_1241_ltmage_2.description: A Spire Caster with experience in war. Specializes in causing extreme area damage under relatively stable conditions. While highly confident, they are still vulnerable to interference from external energy.
enemy_1241_ltmage_2.ability: Attacks 2 targets at once; When attacking targets outside of Realigned Flux, deals <@eb.key>splash damage</>

enemy_1242_ltsmag.name: Remnant Violinist
enemy_1242_ltsmag.description: Cunning remnants of the Witch King, they were once violinists of a certain orchestra in the capital. Years of lying low have honed their observational prowess, and they will make use of anything to defeat their enemies.
enemy_1242_ltsmag.ability: Attacks can travel along Realigned Flux, dealing damage to <@eb.key>all connected</> units

enemy_1242_ltsmag_2.name: Remnant Principal Violinist
enemy_1242_ltsmag_2.description: Scheming remnants of the Witch King, they were once the principal violinist of a certain orchestra in the capital. It's said that they stole their position from another by forcing the stage setup to be changed.
enemy_1242_ltsmag_2.ability: Attacks can travel along Realigned Flux, dealing damage to <@eb.key>all connected</> units

enemy_1243_ltswar.name: Remnant Saxophonist
enemy_1243_ltswar.description: Irritable remnants of the Witch King, they once attempted to bribe their way into a certain orchestra in the capital. After many years of lying low, they have lost much of their sanity and now try to tear their enemies apart using music itself.
enemy_1243_ltswar.ability: When blowing at full force, fires ranged attacks in all 4 directions, dealing <@eb.key>high Physical damage</> to allies hit. These attacks can be blocked by Realigned Flux

enemy_1243_ltswar_2.name: Remnant Official Saxophonist
enemy_1243_ltswar_2.description: Hysterical remnants of the Witch King, they once spent large sums of money to join a certain orchestra in the capital, yet were too impatient to arrange a rehearsal of the saxophone concerto with their sponsor.
enemy_1243_ltswar_2.ability: When blowing at full force, fires ranged attacks in all 4 directions, dealing <@eb.key>high Physical damage</> to allies hit. These attacks can be blocked by Realigned Flux

enemy_1244_ltssch.name: Remnant Field Caster
enemy_1244_ltssch.description: Stubborn remnants of the Witch King, they were once the composer of a certain orchestra in the capital. During their many years of lying low, they researched vile arts nearly lost to mankind, staining their hands red with blood, yet they have little to show for it.
enemy_1244_ltssch.ability: Prioritizes targets on Realigned Flux, <@eb.key>Stunning</> them and continually dealing Arts damage while cutting off nearby Realigned Flux

enemy_1244_ltssch_2.name: Remnant Elite Field Caster
enemy_1244_ltssch_2.description: Unrepentant remnants of the Witch King, they were once the sponsor of a certain orchestra in the capital. There are whispers of connections to the Spire, but most of these turned out to be nothing more than far-fetched rumors.
enemy_1244_ltssch_2.ability: Prioritizes targets on Realigned Flux, <@eb.key>Stunning</> them and continually dealing Arts damage while cutting off nearby Realigned Flux

enemy_1246_aslime.name: Blackwater Originium Slug
enemy_1246_aslime.description: A wild infected creature that normally lives in the nomadic city's sewers, it has surfaced after being provoked. It emits an unpleasant odor, but what's more vexing is that no one knows where they will pop up from next.

enemy_1246_aslime_2.name: Blackwater Originium Slug α
enemy_1246_aslime_2.description: A wild infected creature that is more dangerous than a normal Blackwater Originium Slug. It normally lives in the nomadic city's sewers, but has surfaced after being provoked. Both its striking odor and its elusiveness often catch people off-guard.

enemy_1247_ltgtld.name: Dame Gertrude
enemy_1247_ltgtld.description: Gertrude Strollo, Lehnsfrau of Vyseheim and a researcher of energy induction and redirection. Suffers from chronic insomnia and often goes without sleep.
enemy_1247_ltgtld.ability: Attacks <@eb.key>2 targets</> at once and <@eb.key>cannot be blocked</>; Can create <@eb.key>Virtual Images</> at the current position

enemy_1249_lysdb.name: 莱茵生命防卫科成员
enemy_1249_lysdb.description: 莱茵生命的护卫人员。配备莱茵生命为其提供的防暴装置，经过防暴作战训练，具有一定的护卫能力。
enemy_1249_lysdb.ability: 可以抵挡一次物理或法术伤害

enemy_1249_lysdb_2.name: 莱茵生命防卫科高级成员
enemy_1249_lysdb_2.description: 莱茵生命的警卫人员。配备莱茵生命为其提供的防暴装置，经过特级防暴作战训练，护卫能力大大增强。
enemy_1249_lysdb_2.ability: 可以抵挡一次物理或法术伤害

enemy_1250_lyengs.name: 莱茵生命工程科成员
enemy_1250_lyengs.description: 莱茵生命的工程师。负责提供设备或在生产设备时提出专业意见，在事务上与能量科成员关系密切。
enemy_1250_lyengs.ability: 攻击造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>，持续为未激活的R系列动力装甲恢复生命值

enemy_1250_lyengs_2.name: 莱茵生命高级工程科成员
enemy_1250_lyengs_2.description: 莱茵生命的高级工程师。能量科为莱茵生命争取到了越来越多的哥伦比亚官方资源，工程科成员以此为机会，设计并生产出更多精尖设备。
enemy_1250_lyengs_2.ability: 攻击造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>，持续为未激活的R系列动力装甲恢复生命值

enemy_1251_lysyta.name: Dor-1号失败品
enemy_1251_lysyta.description: 多萝西实验失败的产物。一团形状不规则的银色物体，散发着柔和的光芒，仿佛一个沉睡着的梦境。
enemy_1251_lysyta.ability: 接触未激活的R系列动力装甲时，为其回复一定技力

enemy_1251_lysyta_2.name: Dor-α号失败品
enemy_1251_lysyta_2.description: 多萝西实验失败的产物。一团形状不规则的银色物体，散发着柔和的光芒，但它不常见的外表仍旧让人下意识地惧怕，想要远离。
enemy_1251_lysyta_2.ability: 接触未激活的R系列动力装甲时，为其回复一定技力

enemy_1252_lysytb.name: Dor-2号复制体
enemy_1252_lysytb.description: 多萝西再次实验所得的产物。当它第一次被制造出来时，多萝西沉醉于它的美丽。
enemy_1252_lysytb.ability: 接触未激活的R系列动力装甲时，为其回复一定技力

enemy_1252_lysytb_2.name: Dor-β号复制体
enemy_1252_lysytb_2.description: 多萝西再次实验所得的产物。即使没能达到预期效果，多萝西仍然充满希望。
enemy_1252_lysytb_2.ability: 接触未激活的R系列动力装甲时，为其回复一定技力

enemy_1253_lysytc.name: Dor-3号改造体
enemy_1253_lysytc.description: 多萝西私自实验产出的造物。它不仅仅是多萝西的造物，更是她的家人，她的梦想。
enemy_1253_lysytc.ability: 攻击造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>，未被阻挡时，受到的物理或法术伤害减少50%，接触未激活的R系列动力装甲时，为其回复大量技力

enemy_1253_lysytc_2.name: Dor-γ号改造体
enemy_1253_lysytc_2.description: 多萝西私自实验产出的造物。梦想终须反馈回现实，多萝西希望自己能成为温暖的庇护港湾。
enemy_1253_lysytc_2.ability: 攻击造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>，未被阻挡时，受到的物理或法术伤害减少50%，接触未激活的R系列动力装甲时，为其回复大量技力

enemy_1254_lypa.name: 实验用动力装甲
enemy_1254_lypa.description: 无人操控的动力装甲。不需要操控者在其中控制，但灵活度仍旧很高。

enemy_1254_lypa_2.name: 测试用动力装甲
enemy_1254_lypa_2.description: 无人操控的动力装甲。仿佛拥有自主意识一般，就连经验丰富的工程师也很难凭肉眼分辨是否有人操控。

enemy_1255_lybgpa.name: R-31重型动力装甲
enemy_1255_lybgpa.description: 大约半年前出现在某些雇佣兵团体中的型号，性能与五年前军方量产的相当。莱茵生命能量科的项目与多方合作，现在也在争取更多的合作机会。
enemy_1255_lybgpa.ability: 对目标使用【超负载】，大幅提升攻击速度，每次攻击造成物理伤害，并使目标<$ba.stun>晕眩</>

enemy_1255_lybgpa_2.name: R-31a重型动力装甲
enemy_1255_lybgpa_2.description: 大约半年前出现在某些雇佣兵团体中的型号，性能与五年前军方量产的相当。技术不被限定，哥伦比亚人在遵守法律的同时，总是乐意寻求效率更高的方式。
enemy_1255_lybgpa_2.ability: 对目标使用【超负载】，大幅提升攻击速度，每次攻击造成物理伤害，并使目标<$ba.stun>晕眩</>

enemy_1256_lyacpa.name: R-11突击动力装甲
enemy_1256_lyacpa.description: 搭载了远程武器的型号，攻击力大幅度增强。这类实验性质的武器即使技术仍处在原型阶段，威力和能量也绝对不容小觑。

enemy_1256_lyacpa_2.name: R-11a突击动力装甲
enemy_1256_lyacpa_2.description: 搭载了远程武器的型号，攻击力大幅度增强。很难想象这种技术若是可以量产，将会带来怎样的改变。

enemy_1257_lydrty.name: 多萝西
enemy_1257_lydrty.description: 多萝西·弗兰克斯，莱茵生命源石技艺应用科主任。借助科技与理想的力量，她希望人与人之间的差距可以被消除，弱小之人，能得到来自她的庇护。
enemy_1257_lydrty.ability: 无法被阻挡，部署陷阱，踩上去的友方单位受到<@eb.key>法术伤害</>且<$ba.stun>晕眩</>一段时间，撤回保护目标时不扣除关卡生命值

enemy_1258_durman.name: Alcohol Lover
enemy_1258_durman.description: A somewhat tipsy Durin. Just inebriated enough to think they're battling against some evil creature.
enemy_1258_durman.ability: Initially has <@eb.key>100% Physical Dodge</> for a period of time

enemy_1258_durman_2.name: Alcohol Association Member
enemy_1258_durman_2.description: A piss-drunk Durin. 'I'm not drunk! Who said I was drunk? Was it you?!'
enemy_1258_durman_2.ability: Initially has <@eb.key>100% Physical Dodge</> for a period of time

enemy_1259_durwar.name: Lakeside Volunteer
enemy_1259_durwar.description: An amateur lifeguard doing nothing in particular. Because there really was nobody in need of saving, he instead decided to take up boxing, and unexpectedly had quite the talent for it.
enemy_1259_durwar.ability: Upon dropping beneath half HP for the first time, gains <@eb.key>100% Physical Dodge</> for a period of time

enemy_1259_durwar_2.name: Lakeside Lifeguard
enemy_1259_durwar_2.description: A professional lifeguard who goes around shooting the breeze. Strong in stature and bronzed in complexion, one look at him is enough to give a sense of security. But in actuality, he can't swim at all, and got that tan from high-intensity outdoor boxing training.
enemy_1259_durwar_2.ability: Upon dropping beneath half HP for the first time, gains <@eb.key>100% Physical Dodge</> for a period of time

enemy_1260_durmag.name: Sandcastle Builder
enemy_1260_durmag.description: A Durin who has made a hobby out of building sandcastles. He despises those who would kick up the waters of the artificial lake, and so he installed an Arts Unit onto his construction tool.

enemy_1260_durmag_2.name: Sandcastle Architect
enemy_1260_durmag_2.description: A Durin who has made a career out of designing sandcastles. Having accepted the reality that it is impossible to actually build a sandcastle, he has not even been drafting designs recently, instead focusing his efforts on tinkering with the Arts Unit.

enemy_1261_dursho.name: Volleyball Serving Cart
enemy_1261_dursho.description: A volleyball-serving cart designed for use by friendless tourists. However, they see no use at all, as there are far too many people coming to play volleyball.
enemy_1261_dursho.ability: Gains increased ATK with each attack (up to a limit); when affected by certain <$ba.debuff>Negative Statuses</>, these stacks will be lost

enemy_1261_dursho_2.name: Volleyball Spiking Cart
enemy_1261_dursho_2.description: A volleyball-spiking cart designed as a revenge against someone. Continuously makes powerful spikes at nearby people in an attempt to ruin all volleyball matches on the beach.
enemy_1261_dursho_2.ability: Gains increased ATK with each attack (up to a limit); when affected by certain <$ba.debuff>Negative Statuses</>, these stacks will be lost

enemy_1262_durplc.name: Full Metal Surfing Instructor
enemy_1262_durplc.description: A sturdy mechanical surfing instructor that can withstand strong winds and waves. Its weaknesses are twofold: despite its anti-rust coating, it still rusts easily, and also it doesn't float.
enemy_1262_durplc.ability: Can <@eb.key>stop <Self-Driving Carts></>; takes significantly reduced Physical and Arts damage when not blocked

enemy_1262_durplc_2.name: Alloy Surfing Instructor
enemy_1262_durplc_2.description: A sturdy mechanical surfing instructor that can withstand water and corrosion. High-density rare alloys were incorporated to increase its resistance to rust, but as such, it sinks even harder.
enemy_1262_durplc_2.ability: Can <@eb.key>stop <Self-Driving Carts></>; takes significantly reduced Physical and Arts damage when not blocked

enemy_1263_durbus.name: Fully-Enclosed Beach Buggy
enemy_1263_durbus.description: A beach buggy beloved by all. Carries three passengers in addition to the driver. Cool and breezy on the inside, it's perfect for those tuckered out from playing.
enemy_1263_durbus.ability: Can only be blocked by units with at least 3 Block; when next to enemies that are both non-Machine and non-Leader, they will be loaded inside as passengers (up to 3 max), and will be unloaded when this unit is defeated

enemy_1263_durbus_2.name: Competitive-Grade Beach Buggy
enemy_1263_durbus_2.description: A beach buggy beloved by all. Though its capacity is the same, all its other peripherals have been upgraded - in particular, the AC unit that effortlessly makes driver and passengers alike shiver.
enemy_1263_durbus_2.ability: Can only be blocked by units with at least 3 Block; when next to enemies that are both non-Machine and non-Leader, they will be loaded inside as passengers (up to 3 max), and will be unloaded when this unit is defeated

enemy_1264_durgrd.name: Mead-Grade Waker-Upper
enemy_1264_durgrd.description: A powerful machine that sends chills across the beach with its might, providing a complimentary water cannon service for drunkards by the lake. The only downside being that it has no way of actually identifying who is drunk.
enemy_1264_durgrd.ability: Upon taking damage for the first time, gains significantly increased ASPD and Movement Speed for a period of time

enemy_1264_durgrd_2.name: Whiskey-Grade Waker-Upper
enemy_1264_durgrd_2.description: A terrifying machine that sweeps across the beach, equipped with an ultra-powerful water cannon strong enough to blast any drunkard to their senses. After someone secretly tampered with its targeting logic, it now only blasts sober people.
enemy_1264_durgrd_2.ability: Upon taking damage for the first time, gains significantly increased ASPD and Movement Speed for a period of time

enemy_1265_durcar.name: Self-Driving Cart
enemy_1265_durcar.description: A modular self-driving cart popular throughout Zeruertza. Order yours today and we'll include an additional 'Kaboom Augment! Self-Driver Siege Mode' starter model, for no additional cost!
enemy_1265_durcar.ability: Upon colliding with an enemy unit, inflicts <@eb.key>Physical damage that ignores Dodge</> and a brief <$ba.stun>Stun</>; can be equipped with components to gain additional effects

enemy_1266_nhapos.name: 食腐使徒
enemy_1266_nhapos.description: 食腐者大军成员之一，生存时间越久，越难以击倒。在传言中，他们能吸取敌人的力量，直到自身成长为一种最可怖的存在。
enemy_1266_nhapos.ability: 从“汲营枯枝”出场时，击倒过的敌人越多，<@eb.key>生命、攻击和防御会越强</>；释放<@eb.key>污染秽蚀</>，使周围我方持续损失生命

enemy_1267_nhpbr.name: 萨卡兹枯朽战士
enemy_1267_nhpbr.description: 食腐者大军成员之一，已被污染侵蚀，即使死亡也无法阻断他们对周围土地的污染。在倒下后，腐躯仍旧存在。
enemy_1267_nhpbr.ability: 被击倒时释放<@eb.key>污染秽蚀</>，使周围我方持续损失生命

enemy_1267_nhpbr_2.name: 萨卡兹枯朽战士组长
enemy_1267_nhpbr_2.description: 食腐者大军精锐成员之一，周身已被污染彻底侵蚀，死亡只会让他们造成更多污染，被污染的土地任何生灵都难以存活。在倒下后，腐躯难以彻底消失。
enemy_1267_nhpbr_2.ability: 被击倒时释放<@eb.key>污染秽蚀</>，使周围我方持续损失生命

enemy_1268_nhnrs.name: 萨卡兹枯朽术师
enemy_1268_nhnrs.description: 食腐者大军成员之一，在攻击敌人的同时，他们掌握了一部分治愈同类的力量。吞噬是食腐的起点，共享为生命的最终合流。
enemy_1268_nhnrs.ability: 攻击造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>，持续为<@eb.key>汲营枯枝</>恢复生命值

enemy_1268_nhnrs_2.name: 萨卡兹枯朽术师组长
enemy_1268_nhnrs_2.description: 食腐者大军精锐成员之一，在攻击敌人的同时，他们完全掌握了治愈同类的力量。吞噬是食腐的起点，共享为生命的最终合流。
enemy_1268_nhnrs_2.ability: 攻击造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>，持续为<@eb.key>汲营枯枝</>恢复生命值

enemy_1269_nhfly.name: 枯朽之种
enemy_1269_nhfly.description: 食腐者之王的源石技艺造物，并无思想，却具有自毁性。死亡为食腐的基本，它们创造死亡。
enemy_1269_nhfly.ability: <@eb.key>【飞行单位】</>，接近干员时，自毁并对其造成物理伤害

enemy_1269_nhfly_2.name: 腐败之种
enemy_1269_nhfly_2.description: 食腐者之王的源石技艺造物，枯枝违背常理，摒弃苏生，直奔死亡。死亡为食腐的基本，它们创造死亡。
enemy_1269_nhfly_2.ability: <@eb.key>【飞行单位】</>，接近干员时，自毁并对其造成物理伤害

enemy_1270_nhstlk.name: 逐腐兽
enemy_1270_nhstlk.description: 食腐者之王的源石技艺造物，拥有较快的速度，无法理解何为治愈。制造死亡为它们生命的全部，因此当治愈的力量出现时，它们的能力将在目标身上失去效果。
enemy_1270_nhstlk.ability: <@eb.key>行动速度较快</>，攻击使目标在一段时间内持续受到法术伤害，目标接受治疗时<@eb.key>解除此效果</>

enemy_1270_nhstlk_2.name: 疯狂的逐腐兽
enemy_1270_nhstlk_2.description: 食腐者之王的源石技艺造物，即使停下行动，也无法理解何为治愈。制造死亡为它们生命的全部，思考不被死亡容纳，它们不会停下。
enemy_1270_nhstlk_2.ability: <@eb.key>行动速度较快</>，攻击使目标在一段时间内持续受到法术伤害，目标接受治疗时<@eb.key>解除此效果</>

enemy_1271_nhkodo.name: 萨卡兹枯朽吞噬者
enemy_1271_nhkodo.description: 食腐者大军成员之一，能够吞噬前进路上的阻挡者。生者也可以被吞噬，只要是能够汲取力量的，皆为食粮。
enemy_1271_nhkodo.ability: 首次被阻挡时吞噬阻挡者，<@eb.key>防御力</>大幅提升但<@eb.key>移动速度</>下降，被击倒时干员返回

enemy_1271_nhkodo_2.name: 萨卡兹枯朽吸纳者
enemy_1271_nhkodo_2.description: 食腐者大军精锐成员之一，能够吞噬前进路上的阻挡者，直至自身死亡才被迫返还。生者也可以被吞噬，只要是能够汲取力量的，皆为食粮。
enemy_1271_nhkodo_2.ability: 首次被阻挡时吞噬阻挡者，<@eb.key>防御力</>大幅提升但<@eb.key>移动速度</>下降，被击倒时干员返回

enemy_1272_nhtank.name: 萨卡兹枯朽战车
enemy_1272_nhtank.description: 食腐者大军军事装备之一，为大军行进扫清地面上的阻碍。即便在攻战上它的能力不容小觑，污染仍旧是它的主要职责。
enemy_1272_nhtank.ability: <@eb.key>只攻击地面单位</>，近战攻击造成<@eb.key>更高伤害</>，数次攻击后，下次攻击释放<@eb.key>污染秽蚀</>

enemy_1272_nhtank_2.name: 尖端萨卡兹枯朽战车
enemy_1272_nhtank_2.description: 食腐者大军军事高级装备之一，为大军行进扫清地面上的阻碍，距离越近，它的攻击力越高。即便在攻战上它的能力不容小觑，污染仍旧是它的主要职责。
enemy_1272_nhtank_2.ability: <@eb.key>只攻击地面单位</>，近战攻击造成<@eb.key>更高伤害</>，数次攻击后，下次攻击释放<@eb.key>污染秽蚀</>

enemy_1273_stmgun.name: 伦蒂尼姆城防自行炮
enemy_1273_stmgun.description: 伦蒂尼姆的城防武器之一，拥有较大的攻击范围。规模较大，由伦蒂尼姆的工人们在工厂中组装而成。
enemy_1273_stmgun.ability: 攻击范围较远，会锁定<@eb.key>生命上限最高</>的目标进行数次轰炸，每次对范围内<@eb.key>当前生命比例最高</>的单位造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>

enemy_1273_stmgun_2.name: 高准度伦蒂尼姆城防自行炮
enemy_1273_stmgun_2.description: 伦蒂尼姆的城防武器之一，拥有极大攻击范围的同时，精准度也大幅度提升。规模巨大，由伦蒂尼姆的工人们在工厂中组装而成。
enemy_1273_stmgun_2.ability: 攻击范围较远，会锁定<@eb.key>生命上限最高</>的目标进行数次轰炸，每次对范围内<@eb.key>当前生命比例最高</>的单位造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>

enemy_1274_stmram.name: 蒸汽战车
enemy_1274_stmram.description: 使用维多利亚引以为傲的蒸汽技术制造而成的战车，往往在即将被击垮时爆发出强大的作战能力。
enemy_1274_stmram.ability: 生命值降至一半时<@eb.key>攻击速度</>和<@eb.key>移动速度</>大幅提升，且免疫大部分控制效果

enemy_1274_stmram_2.name: 极温蒸汽战车
enemy_1274_stmram_2.description: 使用维多利亚引以为傲的蒸汽技术制造而成的高级战车，往往在即将被击垮时爆发出强大的作战能力，极少有方法能在最后关头控制住它的暴走。
enemy_1274_stmram_2.ability: 生命值降至一半时<@eb.key>攻击速度</>和<@eb.key>移动速度</>大幅提升，且免疫大部分控制效果

enemy_1275_dwlock.name: 萨卡兹王庭军术师
enemy_1275_dwlock.description: 萨卡兹王庭军术师，萨卡兹的巫术在战场上常常要比许多机械军事设备更加难以应对。他们的作战风格既有萨卡兹特色，又更具纪律性。
enemy_1275_dwlock.ability: 攻击额外造成<@eb.key>凋亡损伤</>，会锁定我方单位持续造成法术伤害，并在释放完成时造成<@eb.key>群体凋亡损伤</>

enemy_1275_dwlock_2.name: 萨卡兹王庭军精锐术师
enemy_1275_dwlock_2.description: 萨卡兹王庭精锐军术师，萨卡兹的巫术在战场上常常要比许多机械军事设备更加难以应对。除却纪律性，在近几年的训练中，他们也表现出了极强的专业性。
enemy_1275_dwlock_2.ability: 攻击额外造成<@eb.key>凋亡损伤</>，会锁定我方单位持续造成法术伤害，并在释放完成时造成<@eb.key>群体凋亡损伤</>

enemy_1276_telex.name: 特雷西斯
enemy_1276_telex.description: 特雷西斯，卡兹戴尔摄政王。已于伦蒂尼姆召集萨卡兹大军，并占领碎片大厦。如果无法阻止他向大公爵宣战，全面战争一触即发。
enemy_1276_telex.ability: 无法被攻击、消失时不会扣除关卡生命值；击倒一切拦路的目标

enemy_1277_sgman.name: 家族士兵
enemy_1277_sgman.description: 家族基层成员，听从高层的命令行事，从不过问。他们的性命并不重要，但他们的死亡足以成为家族寻仇的理由。
enemy_1277_sgman.ability: 被击倒时，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>略微增加

enemy_1277_sgman_2.name: 家族精英士兵
enemy_1277_sgman_2.description: 久经战场的家族基层成员，拳脚强劲，称得上是一流的打手。他们下葬的时候家族会送来吊唁信，但也仅此而已了。
enemy_1277_sgman_2.ability: 被击倒时，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>小幅增加

enemy_1278_sgbow.name: 家族弩手
enemy_1278_sgbow.description: 家族训练的弩手，能从一定距离外发起攻击。家族配置的弩难称精良，所以收到紧急命令时，为了完成任务他们会用上不知从哪学来的简单法术。
enemy_1278_sgbow.ability: <@eb.key>“清算时刻”</>状态下，攻击变为法术伤害

enemy_1278_sgbow_2.name: 家族精英弩手
enemy_1278_sgbow_2.description: 经验丰富的家族弩手，他们的射击更加精准，自然更加致命。家族总是遵守规则的，并没有因此就给他们换上更好的弩，法术仍然必不可少。
enemy_1278_sgbow_2.ability: <@eb.key>“清算时刻”</>状态下，攻击变为法术伤害

enemy_1279_sgbdg.name: 家族恫吓者
enemy_1279_sgbdg.description: 家族训练的大力士，强壮的身材相当唬人。实际上比起拳头，家族更看重的是他们对叙拉古文明用语的充分掌握。
enemy_1279_sgbdg.ability: <@eb.key>能吸引敌人攻击自己</>；被击倒时，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>增加

enemy_1279_sgbdg_2.name: 家族强暴恫吓者
enemy_1279_sgbdg_2.description: 格外强壮的家族大力士，以火爆的脾气闻名大街小巷。他不会吝惜对他人直系亲属的频繁问候，但在关键问题上，他的嘴比最坚硬的岩石还要牢固。
enemy_1279_sgbdg_2.ability: <@eb.key>能吸引敌人攻击自己</>；被击倒时，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>增加

enemy_1280_sgmag.name: 家族术师
enemy_1280_sgmag.description: 家族训练的术师，源石技艺是他们在家族中立身的根本。虽然源石技艺的水平一般，煽动仇恨他们却是一把好手。
enemy_1280_sgmag.ability: 同时攻击两个目标。可以停止攻击，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>持续增加

enemy_1280_sgmag_2.name: 家族精英术师
enemy_1280_sgmag_2.description: 技艺精湛的家族术师，往往能改变战场的局势。尽管自诩地位不低，但大家都知道，没了家族的庇护他们什么也不是。
enemy_1280_sgmag_2.ability: 同时攻击两个目标。可以停止攻击，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>持续增加

enemy_1281_sgcar.name: 家族专用轿车
enemy_1281_sgcar.description: 家族中最常见的交通工具，内饰和外表一样普通，被加固的只有保险杠。除了代步，他们也会用这种轿车送家族的敌人“一路顺风”。
enemy_1281_sgcar.ability: 被击倒时若已被阻挡，将卸下三个<@eb.key>家族士兵</>

enemy_1281_sgcar_2.name: 家族豪华轿车
enemy_1281_sgcar_2.description: 家族中较为少见的交通工具，外表低调但内饰豪华。通常只用来招待家族最为尊贵的宾客，并向他们传达家族某位高层的致意。
enemy_1281_sgcar_2.ability: 被击倒时若已被阻挡，将卸下三个<@eb.key>家族精英士兵</>

enemy_1282_sgelder.name: 家族角头
enemy_1282_sgelder.description: 家族分部的领导者，德高望重，在家族中有不小的威势。传闻说他武器从不离身，但谁都不知道他把武器藏在了哪里，总不可能在雪茄里吧。
enemy_1282_sgelder.ability: 范围内有敌方单位被击倒时，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>增加

enemy_1282_sgelder_2.name: 家族铁腕角头
enemy_1282_sgelder_2.description: 手段强硬的分部领导者，得到了许多家族成员的敬畏。家族兴起时他即存在，在潮流中安然屹立至今，似乎永远也不会倒下。
enemy_1282_sgelder_2.ability: 范围内有敌方单位被击倒时，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>增加

enemy_1283_sgkill.name: 家族灭迹人
enemy_1283_sgkill.description: 忠于家族的强大杀手，于阴影中来去，留下的只有死亡。人人都知晓他的称号，却从未有人谈论他。
enemy_1283_sgkill.ability: <@eb.key>“清算时刻”</>状态下，自身获得额外增强。<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>

enemy_1283_sgkill_2.name: 家族暗影灭迹人
enemy_1283_sgkill_2.description: 忠于家族的顶尖杀手，暗影是他的仆从，杀戮比覆手更轻易。令家族立足与兴盛的秘闻之中都有他的身影，得见他真容的人都已长眠于地下。
enemy_1283_sgkill_2.ability: <@eb.key>“清算时刻”</>状态下，自身获得额外增强。<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>

enemy_1284_sgprst.name: 阿格尼尔神父
enemy_1284_sgprst.description: 阿格尼尔，萨科塔出身的神父，叙拉古统一秩序的建立者之一。别犹豫，他不一定站在你的对立面，但他的铳从不迟疑。顺带一提，他最爱的眼罩是龙门制造的。
enemy_1284_sgprst.ability: 使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>逐渐增加；<@eb.key>“清算时刻”</>状态下，可以无视攻击距离。使用弹药攻击降低目标护甲，弹药上限：<@eb.key>10</>

enemy_1285_sgwlf.name: “与我无关”
enemy_1285_sgwlf.description: 大摇大摆走出来的醉汉，帽子压得很低。至于战场上多出来的燃烧弹，反正与他无关。在口供里他向来都是如此陈述的。
enemy_1285_sgwlf.ability: 每损失一定生命值，释放一个不会消失的燃烧区域。在燃烧区域中的我方干员每秒会受到真实伤害

enemy_3004_speople.name: 叙拉古平民
enemy_3004_speople.description: 看上去像是意外闯入的叙拉古平民，明明战斗前已经疏散了群众，他们还是误入了激烈的战场。不知为何，只要他们出了意外，所有人的怒火就会降临在你身上。
enemy_3004_speople.ability: 撤回保护目标时不扣除关卡生命值；在场时使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>缓慢减少，但死亡时使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>大幅增加

enemy_1286_dumcy.name: 特别行动队士兵
enemy_1286_dumcy.description: 长期受雇于维多利亚贵族的佣兵。时常借助地形隐藏自己的行动。

enemy_1286_dumcy_2.name: 特别行动队队长
enemy_1286_dumcy_2.description: 长期受雇于维多利亚贵族的佣兵队长，拥有更丰富的作战经验。时常借助地形隐藏自己的行动。

enemy_1287_ducrb.name: 沼泽钳兽
enemy_1287_ducrb.description: 维多利亚南部沼泽地区大量出没的感染生物，时常随机攻击荒野上的行路人，是附近居民的威胁。
enemy_1287_ducrb.ability: 免疫沼泽地段影响，在沼泽地段中移动速度提升

enemy_1287_ducrb_2.name: 狂暴沼泽钳兽
enemy_1287_ducrb_2.description: 维多利亚南部沼泽地区大量出没的感染生物，比一般钳兽更加主动地攻击荒野上的行路人，是附近居民的巨大威胁。
enemy_1287_ducrb_2.ability: 免疫沼泽地段影响，在沼泽地段中移动速度提升

enemy_1288_duskls.name: 深池逐火战士
enemy_1288_duskls.description: 附着了领袖火焰的深池部队战士。他们已经死亡，只有身躯在法术的操纵下践行着最后的渴望，一次又一次地站起。
enemy_1288_duskls.ability: 位于燃烧的芦苇丛附近时攻击额外造成<$ba.dt.burning>灼燃损伤</>；被击倒时暂时变为<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>、需要<@eb.key>5</>次伤害击倒的<@eb.key>怨恨的余烬</>，一段时间后重生

enemy_1288_duskls_2.name: 深池逐火精锐战士
enemy_1288_duskls_2.description: 附着了领袖火焰的深池部队精锐战士。更加执着地追逐着领袖的火焰，被法术操纵着不断站起。
enemy_1288_duskls_2.ability: 位于燃烧的芦苇丛附近时攻击额外造成<$ba.dt.burning>灼燃损伤</>；被击倒时暂时变为<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>、需要<@eb.key>5</>次伤害击倒的<@eb.key>暴怒的余烬</>，一段时间后重生

enemy_1289_dubmb.name: 深池弩炮手
enemy_1289_dubmb.description: 深池部队中的远程作战单位。使用的武器改装自维多利亚军方的制式弩箭，加装了能够使用爆炸弹药的发射器。
enemy_1289_dubmb.ability: 攻击2次后，下一次攻击造成<@eb.key>溅射</>伤害

enemy_1289_dubmb_2.name: 深池弩炮队长
enemy_1289_dubmb_2.description: 深池部队远程作战小队的队长。使用的武器改装自维多利亚军方的制式弩箭，加装了能够使用爆炸弹药的发射器，弹药威力更大。
enemy_1289_dubmb_2.ability: 攻击2次后，下一次攻击造成<@eb.key>溅射</>伤害

enemy_1290_duflm.name: 深池引火者
enemy_1290_duflm.description: 深池部队中擅长操纵火焰的术师，燃烧自己身边的一切，甚至自己的死亡。
enemy_1290_duflm.ability: 攻击会点燃目标所在芦苇丛；被击倒时对周围所有我方单位造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>并点燃芦苇丛

enemy_1290_duflm_2.name: 深池引火者队长
enemy_1290_duflm_2.description: 深池部队中极其擅长操纵火焰的精锐术师，燃烧自己身边的一切，甚至自己的死亡。
enemy_1290_duflm_2.ability: 攻击会点燃目标所在芦苇丛；被击倒时对周围所有我方单位造成<@eb.key>法术伤害</>并点燃芦苇丛

enemy_1291_dusrch.name: 沼泽探照车
enemy_1291_dusrch.description: 能够在沼泽地带平稳行驶的军用载具，搭载了先进的侦测设备。
enemy_1291_dusrch.ability: 免疫沼泽地段影响，使周围我方单位的<$ba.camou>迷彩</>和<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>效果失效

enemy_1291_dusrch_2.name: 重型沼泽探照车
enemy_1291_dusrch_2.description: 能够在沼泽地带平稳行驶的军用载具，搭载了先进的侦测设备，强化了车身防护。
enemy_1291_dusrch_2.ability: 免疫沼泽地段影响，使周围我方单位的<$ba.camou>迷彩</>和<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>效果失效

enemy_1292_duskld.name: 深池逐火护卫
enemy_1292_duskld.description: 附着了领袖火焰的深池部队防御者。他们已经死亡，但灌注法术的武装还在支撑着他们为自己的野心战斗。
enemy_1292_duskld.ability: 位于燃烧的芦苇丛附近时攻击额外造成<$ba.dt.burning>灼燃损伤</>且受到的物理与法术伤害降低；被击倒时暂时变为<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>、需要<@eb.key>10</>次伤害击倒的<@eb.key>贪欲的火灰</>，一段时间后重生

enemy_1292_duskld_2.name: 深池逐火精锐护卫
enemy_1292_duskld_2.description: 附着了领袖火焰的深池部队精锐防御者。更加执着地追逐着领袖的火焰，灌注法术的武装使他们难以被打倒。
enemy_1292_duskld_2.ability: 位于燃烧的芦苇丛附近时攻击额外造成<$ba.dt.burning>灼燃损伤</>且受到的物理与法术伤害降低；被击倒时暂时变为<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>、需要<@eb.key>10</>次伤害击倒的<@eb.key>狂妄的火灰</>，一段时间后重生

enemy_1293_duswrd.name: 深池护卫队成员
enemy_1293_duswrd.description: “校官”率领的部队成员。擅长突击战与攻坚战，纪律严明，绝无二心。
enemy_1293_duswrd.ability: 点燃经过的芦苇丛，3次攻击后对目标发动五次连续斩击

enemy_1293_duswrd_2.name: 深池护卫队精锐成员
enemy_1293_duswrd_2.description: “校官”率领的部队精锐成员。突击战与攻坚战中的核心，纪律严明，绝无二心。
enemy_1293_duswrd_2.ability: 点燃经过的芦苇丛，3次攻击后对目标发动五次连续斩击

enemy_1293_duswrd_3.name: “校官”
enemy_1293_duswrd_3.description: “校官”，深池高级军官，赤铁近卫队队长。以历经战火的锋刃，在混乱中斩出他认定的唯一秩序。
enemy_1293_duswrd_3.ability: 点燃经过的芦苇丛，3次攻击后对目标发动五次强力斩击

enemy_1295_ymph.name: 谛兽
enemy_1295_ymph.description: “睚”随手捏塑的造物。躯体与黄沙同色，听觉极其敏锐，穿街过巷如影随形，负责情报的收集与传递。

enemy_1295_ymph_2.name: 躁怒谛兽
enemy_1295_ymph_2.description: “睚”随手捏塑的造物，被黄沙洗练出凶意，听觉极其敏锐，穿街过巷如影随形，负责情报的收集与传递，并参与战斗。

enemy_1296_ymknif.name: 山海众散兵
enemy_1296_ymknif.description: 成分复杂的普通山海众成员。凭着“山海八荒，尽归其主”的夸张口号，山海众蛊惑了一大批流寇匪徒，在炎国境内到处滋事。
enemy_1296_ymknif.ability: 位于<@eb.key>玉门天灾工事</>上时攻击范围扩大

enemy_1296_ymknif_2.name: 山海众游勇
enemy_1296_ymknif_2.description: 成分复杂的普通山海众成员。凭着“山海八荒，尽归其主”的夸张口号，山海众蛊惑了一大批流寇匪徒，在炎国境内到处滋事，不少人身上都背着官司。
enemy_1296_ymknif_2.ability: 位于<@eb.key>玉门天灾工事</>上时攻击范围扩大

enemy_1297_ymflag.name: 山海众传令手
enemy_1297_ymflag.description: 负责传达作战指令的山海众成员。山海众的队伍似乎拥有一套完备的密语系统，显然接受过专业的信息训练，并非乌合之众。
enemy_1297_ymflag.ability: 在首个可部署的<@eb.key>玉门天灾工事</>上部署<@eb.key>山海密语仪</>

enemy_1297_ymflag_2.name: 山海众掌令使
enemy_1297_ymflag_2.description: 负责分析情报、下达作战指令的山海众成员。山海众的队伍似乎拥有一套完备的密语系统，显然接受过专业的信息训练，并非乌合之众。
enemy_1297_ymflag_2.ability: 在首个可部署的<@eb.key>玉门天灾工事</>上部署<@eb.key>山海密语仪</>

enemy_1298_ymmonk.name: 山海众冒矢者
enemy_1298_ymmonk.description: 负责防御的山海众成员。山海众网罗了不少亡命之徒，他们身材魁梧，手持重盾，为同伙提供庇护。

enemy_1298_ymmonk_2.name: 山海众连阵者
enemy_1298_ymmonk_2.description: 负责防御的山海众成员。山海众网罗了不少亡命之徒，他们大多曾为祸一方，身材魁梧，手持特制的重盾，极具威慑力。

enemy_1299_ymkilr.name: 山海众头目
enemy_1299_ymkilr.description: 隐于队伍之中的山海众头目。神出鬼没，残忍果决，“信仰”之下，究竟是迷狂的妄念，还是可笑的私欲？
enemy_1299_ymkilr.ability: <$ba.invisible>隐匿</>，隐匿效果失效后的下一次攻击造成更高伤害

enemy_1299_ymkilr_2.name: 山海众秘使
enemy_1299_ymkilr_2.description: 似乎身负神秘任务的山海众头目。神出鬼没，心狠手辣，对手下的牺牲也不以为意。他们的信仰在迷雾之中，他们究竟所图为何？
enemy_1299_ymkilr_2.ability: <$ba.invisible>隐匿</>，隐匿效果失效后的下一次攻击造成更高伤害

enemy_1300_ymmir.name: 山海众窥魅人
enemy_1300_ymmir.description: 能施展奇异术法的山海众成员。他们迷信那些庞大生灵的力量，他们高呼“山海八荒，尽归其主”，施展着一鳞半爪的“神力”。
enemy_1300_ymmir.ability: 攻击造成法术伤害，会持续锁定我方单位并在释放完成时造成一次高额法术伤害，之后攻击速度提升

enemy_1300_ymmir_2.name: 山海众司魅人
enemy_1300_ymmir_2.description: 能施展奇异术法的山海众成员。他们迷信那些庞大生灵的力量，怨恨自己的同胞，他们高呼“山海八荒，尽归其主”，施展着来历不明的“神力”。
enemy_1300_ymmir_2.ability: 攻击造成法术伤害，会持续锁定我方单位并在释放完成时造成一次高额法术伤害，之后攻击速度提升

enemy_1301_ymcnon.name: “破坚”
enemy_1301_ymcnon.description: 由炎国工部监造司专为玉门城设计打造的弩炮塔，被潜入的山海众劫持。玉门横行沙海之上，前行无阻，坚石可破。
enemy_1301_ymcnon.ability: 优先攻击位于<@eb.key>玉门天灾工事</>上的我方单位

enemy_1301_ymcnon_2.name: “碎壁”
enemy_1301_ymcnon_2.description: 由炎国工部监造司专为玉门城设计打造的加强弩炮塔，被潜入的山海众劫持。玉门横行沙海之上，前行无阻，铁壁难存。
enemy_1301_ymcnon_2.ability: 优先攻击位于<@eb.key>玉门天灾工事</>上的我方单位

enemy_1302_ymtro.name: “履平沙”
enemy_1302_ymtro.description: 由炎国工部监造司专为玉门城设计打造的运兵车，被潜入的山海众劫持。可载四名士兵，即使是沙漠地形亦能平稳运行。
enemy_1302_ymtro.ability: 只能被阻挡数大于等于4的单位阻挡；周围有领袖以外的非机械敌人时会将其装载为乘客（最多4个），首次到达<@eb.key>云梯</>时释放装载的乘客

enemy_1302_ymtro_2.name: “越长尘”
enemy_1302_ymtro_2.description: 由炎国工部监造司专为玉门城设计打造的第二批运兵车，被潜入的山海众劫持。可载四名士兵，即使是沙漠地形亦能平稳、快速地运行，可高效配合城防作战。
enemy_1302_ymtro_2.ability: 只能被阻挡数大于等于4的单位阻挡；周围有领袖以外的非机械敌人时会将其装载为乘客（最多4个），首次到达<@eb.key>云梯</>时释放装载的乘客

enemy_2001_duckmi.name: Duck Lord
enemy_2001_duckmi.description: A famous Columbian investor, entrepreneur, and master of 'Duck Power.' Out of the public eye, enjoys kicking back with others...
enemy_2001_duckmi.ability: Does not deduct Life Points when spared; Cannot be Blocked; Has significantly increased Movement Speed after being attacked

enemy_2002_bearmi.name: Gopnik
enemy_2002_bearmi.description: The Ursus security guard hired by Duck Lord. Powerful, but not very smart. Mainly responsible for carrying luggage for Duck Lord.
enemy_2002_bearmi.ability: Does not deduct Life Points when spared; Cannot be <$ba.stun>Stunned</>

enemy_2034_sythef.name: 流泪小子
enemy_2034_sythef.description: 唯唯诺诺的佩洛，离开家庭后正在寻找自己的新生活......不过别人是记不住那么多的，别人只知道他一直在流泪。
enemy_2034_sythef.ability: 进入目标点也不会损失目标生命；<$ba.invisible>隐匿</>，攻击会<$ba.stun>晕眩</>目标

enemy_2009_csaudc.name: Derisive Audience
enemy_2009_csaudc.description: A diehard fan of the Crimson Troupe, they enjoy the performances night and day. They have become as incomprehensible as the troupe itself.

enemy_2010_csdcr.name: Scarlet Singer
enemy_2010_csdcr.description: A performer of the Crimson Troupe, they unleash their singing voices when sufficiently stimulated, inciting their followers to attack in a frenzy.
enemy_2010_csdcr.ability: Attacks inflict <$ba.dt.neural>Nervous Impairment</>; After receiving a certain number of hits, greatly increases all enemies' ASPD for a short period.

enemy_2011_csppt.name: Theater Golem
enemy_2011_csppt.description: A gigantic golem maintained by the Crimson Troupe's prop department, they are normally used to move bulky items. They are massive and difficult to block.
enemy_2011_csppt.ability: Can only be blocked by units with at least 4 Block; Attacks deal splash damage to allied units in a small area around self.

enemy_2012_csbln.name: 'Small Surprise'
enemy_2012_csbln.description: A special gift prepared by the Crimson Troupe for the audience. Every audience member who receives a gift will become particularly 'ecstatic'.
enemy_2012_csbln.ability: Does not attack; Upon death, deals Arts damage to all surrounding units and inflicts <$ba.dt.neural>Nervous Impairment</>.

enemy_2017_csphts.name: Ominous Apparition
enemy_2017_csphts.description: A patch of shadow. It has never once left, nor has it ever truly existed.
enemy_2017_csphts.ability: Has a chance to dodge Physical and Arts attacks when not blocked; Uses skills to deal Physical damage to the surrounding area; Attacks and skills ignore a certain amount of armor and inflict <$ba.dt.neural>Nervous Impairment</>.

enemy_2021_syfish.name: 骨海漂流体
enemy_2021_syfish.description: 从大群骨骸中诞生的恐鱼，常常成群而动，一边寻找尸骨吞食养分，一边任由其他恐鱼捕食。
enemy_2021_syfish.ability: 攻击额外造成<$ba.dt.erosion>侵蚀损伤</>

enemy_2022_syzeni.name: 固海凿石者
enemy_2022_syzeni.description: 拥有坚固外壳的恐鱼，栖居在大群外围，为整个大群阻挡敌人。
enemy_2022_syzeni.ability: 攻击范围内首次出现我方单位时，停止移动且防御力提升，持续一定时间

enemy_2023_sypult.name: 投嗣育母
enemy_2023_sypult.description: 一种以生育为主要职责的恐鱼，遇到致命威胁时会向敌人投掷拟嗣以便真正的恐鱼幼崽逃离战场。
enemy_2023_sypult.ability: 只能攻击地面目标；造成伤害时，在目标周围召唤1个【注亡拟嗣】

enemy_2024_synut.name: 注亡拟嗣
enemy_2024_synut.description: 它们是母体生命的延伸，外形上与其诞下的幼崽没有区别。
enemy_2024_synut.ability: 无法移动；会逐渐损失生命；攻击额外造成<$ba.dt.erosion>侵蚀损伤</>

enemy_2025_syufo.name: 掠海漂移体
enemy_2025_syufo.description: 一种已初步适应天空环境的恐鱼，能够在不受阻碍的情况下一直在海面上滑行。这一分支持续进化后，或许能够衍生出永久居住在天空的后代。
enemy_2025_syufo.ability: <$ba.float>近地悬浮</>；攻击额外造成<$ba.dt.erosion>侵蚀损伤</>

enemy_2033_syboys.name: 塑路者分形
enemy_2033_syboys.description: 海嗣塑路者所留下的分形。幻影必定消散，路途满是歧误。仍要探索，仍要探索。
enemy_2033_syboys.ability: 只能存活一段时间；每攻击2次后下次攻击召唤1个【塑路者分形】

enemy_2040_syrott.name: 伊莎玛拉之泪
enemy_2040_syrott.description: 伊莎玛拉探索与争斗本质的具象。
enemy_2040_syrott.ability: 出现在我方单位周围；每隔一段时间对目标造成真实伤害，若攻击范围内无目标则为【伊莎玛拉，腐化之心】充能；【伊莎玛拉，腐化之心】变身时消失

enemy_2035_sybox.name: 箱形恐鱼
enemy_2035_sybox.description: 一种拟态成宝箱模样的恐鱼，时常被深海主教用以保卫避难所。

enemy_4001_toxcar.name: Retrofitted Gastruck
enemy_4001_toxcar.description: A pesticide spraying vehicle that used to belong to a large nomadic city. It has been retrofitted by Closure to spray tear gas instead, but she didn't have time to install an IFF system.
enemy_4001_toxcar.ability: When unblocked, all allied units lose HP constantly

enemy_4001_toxcar_2.name: Supercharged Gastruck
enemy_4001_toxcar_2.description: A pesticide spraying vehicle that used to belong to a large nomadic city. It has been retrofitted by Closure to spray tear gas instead, but she didn't have time to install an IFF system. This model has an expanded gas tank and is far more dangerous.
enemy_4001_toxcar_2.ability: When unblocked, all allied units lose HP constantly

enemy_4002_syokai.name: Cheap Second-hand Drone
enemy_4002_syokai.description: Cheap goods sold for scrap from the Kazimierz arenas. Feel free to waste it however you like.
enemy_4002_syokai.ability: When destroyed, grants a deployable unit; Does not count towards the defeated enemies counter.

enemy_4002_syokai_2.name: Remodeled Second-hand Drone
enemy_4002_syokai_2.description: Cheap goods sold for scrap from the Kazimierz arenas. Closure has performed some slight modifications on this batch, but it won't change the fact these are cheap as hell.
enemy_4002_syokai_2.ability: When destroyed, grants a deployable unit; Does not count towards the defeated enemies counter.

enemy_4003_pbank.name: Mobile Power Source
enemy_4003_pbank.description: An experimental prototype developed during the early years of a certain Columbian tech company. The objective was to provide power on the battlefield, however due to the lack of a positioning device, it will often leave by itself if unattended to.
enemy_4003_pbank.ability: Cannot be blocked; When destroyed, recovers the SP of nearby Operators; Does not count towards the defeated enemies counter.

enemy_1050_lslime.name: 'Pompeii'
enemy_1050_lslime.description: A massive infected beast. These aberrations were born in a special high-temperature environment. Nobody wants to approach these creatures due to their grotesque appearance and the extreme heat they give off. The existence of these giant creatures has been known since ancient times, but to see one warped by infection is terrifyingly unforgettable...
enemy_1050_lslime.ability: Attacks up to four targets simultaneously; Ignites targets it attacks, dealing burn damage over time; When blocked, self-immolates to cause high damage; Gains a large amount of ASPD when this unit's HP is under 50%.

enemy_1500_skulsr.name: Skullshatterer
enemy_1500_skulsr.description: One of Reunion's squad leaders who serves in the Assault Squad. Though armed with an Originium launcher and explosives, reports show that he possesses high mobility and poses a significant threat even in melee combat.He has been seen several times around Lungmen, and intel suggests that he is carrying out some special operation in the region.
enemy_1500_skulsr.ability: Launches grenades when not being blocked, reducing the DEF of the primary target and surrounding allied Operators significantly; Increases ATK significantly when HP is under 50%.

enemy_1502_crowns.name: Crownslayer
enemy_1502_crowns.description: One of Reunion's squad leaders who handles infiltration and assassination operations, specializing in melee combat and breaking through defensive lines. Her stealth and superb infiltration abilities have foiled countless attempts to capture her.
enemy_1502_crowns.ability: Can pass through Operators if blocked.

enemy_1503_talula.name: Talulah
enemy_1503_talula.description: The leader and spokesperson of Reunion. So far, she has been confirmed to have masterminded multiple riots, as well as the destruction of Chernobog.
enemy_1503_talula.ability: Long-ranged attacks and [Stellar Corona] deal Arts damage; When blocked, uses melee attacks that deal True damage; Applies [Burning Breath] to one target (Deals increasing True damage each second, but can be <$ba.buffres>resisted</>); When HP drops beneath half, gains greatly increased DEF and RES, and uses Skills more often.

enemy_1504_cqbw.name: W
enemy_1504_cqbw.description: A Sarkaz Mercenary and one of Reunion's squad leaders, she carries around a weapon that resembles a Laterano Gun. However, she almost exclusively attacks using explosives and throwing weapons. One of her common strategies is to attack the enemy's flank using large amounts of active Originium explosives. However, her erratic movements make her almost impossible to predict...
enemy_1504_cqbw.ability: Can use explosives to deal massive physical damage;

enemy_1505_frstar.name: FrostNova
enemy_1505_frstar.description: A Caster who is one of Reunion's squad leaders. She is one of the few Casters capable of suppressing enemies in a head-on engagement. Among the squads she leads, the special 'Yeti Squadron' assists her in some special operations. As her name implies, she has a cold personality.
enemy_1505_frstar.ability: Frequently uses Arts to attack nearby Operators with an Ice Nova, dealing high Arts damage as well as slowing the AS of affected targets; Can also Freeze tiles indefinitely, making it impossible to deploy Operators on these tiles.

enemy_1507_mephi.name: Mephisto
enemy_1507_mephi.description: A Medic who is one of Reunion's squad leaders, often working in tandem with Faust. He heals the wounded while commanding his troops to attack, and can improve their life recovery rate. He boasts a high resistance to Arts. Currently, it has been confirmed that he is the one controlling the Hosts.
enemy_1507_mephi.ability: Doubles the HP regeneration of all enemies on the field; Normal attack heals 3 enemy units at a time.

enemy_1508_faust.name: Faust
enemy_1508_faust.description: A Sniper who is one of Reunion's squad leaders, often working in tandem with Mephisto. He uses extremely long-range attacks to inflict devastating physical damage. He is known to occasionally use special attacks such as summoning turret-like ballistae or launching highly destructive bolts.
enemy_1508_faust.ability: Cannot be blocked and gains invulnerability for a period of time; May attack with a special bolt dealing double damage; Regularly activates hidden turrets around the battlefield.

enemy_1509_mousek.name: 'Rat King'
enemy_1509_mousek.description: Lin, Lin Gray, the Rat King of the slum. He bears many titles, just like the shifting of the city's shadows underneath his feet. Don't touch the red lines. If you ever have a moment of indecisiveness, whatever it is that you were concerned about will become nothing more than a whisper in the winds above the dunes.
enemy_1509_mousek.ability: Greatly increased DEF when the shield is present; targets the unit with the highest Max HP with 'Singing Sands', inflicting massive Physical damage; targets the unit with the lowest Max HP with 'Sand Tomb', reducing the target's ATK and continuously inflicting Arts damage.

enemy_1510_frstar2.name: FrostNova, 'Winter's Scar'
enemy_1510_frstar2.description: Leader of the Yeti Squadron, she has released the remainder of what little life force she has left in preparation for the final battle. The biting cold of the land has already been released; are we truly prepared to make an enemy out of it?
enemy_1510_frstar2.ability: Normal attacks and Ice Novas inflict Arts damage and cause the <$ba.cold>Cold</> effect on affected targets; Ice Nova deals double damage to <$ba.frozen>Frozen</> targets; FrostNova is temporarily invulnerable during her second form, and her attacks and skills are more powerful

enemy_1506_patrt.name: Patriot
enemy_1506_patrt.description: His armor is in disrepair and damaged in many places. The blade of his once sharp halberd is now eroded with rust. However, the indomitable Patriot never capitulates, never backs down, and never shows mercy. He has long struggled with fate, and now resolves to slit the throat of fate.
enemy_1506_patrt.ability: Inspires his troops, greatly increasing their ATK and DEF; In Marching stance, he is extremely vulnerable to attacks; In Ruination stance, he uses long-ranged attacks, is immune to <$ba.stun>Stun</> effects, continuously deals True damage around him, and deals Physical damage to the farthest high ground unit.

enemy_1511_mdrock.name: Mudrock
enemy_1511_mdrock.description: Age unknown, gender unknown, history unknown. This ex-Reunion member now leads an organization of Infected and wanders the wilderness between the cities of Leithanien. What thoughts run through Mudrock's mind as being forced to once again step upon the battlefield?
enemy_1511_mdrock.ability: When attacking, permanently increases ATK, stacking up to 6 times; Has a barrier that absorbs spell damage; While the barrier persists, this unit has greatly increased Max HP and ASPD; Barrier periodically refreshes; Releases a skill that automatically seizes control of the nearest non-enemy controlled 'Gramophone.'

enemy_1512_mcmstr.name: 'The Big Ugly Thing'
enemy_1512_mcmstr.description: Zumama's magnum opus, a massive mechanical monster piloted by the High Priest. It can strike both in melee range and from a distance, capable of easily destroying Giant Mushrooms and Stumps. Normal engineers cannot even fathom how a machine slapped together haphazardly like this can even move, but move it indeed does.
enemy_1512_mcmstr.ability: Periodically destroys Giant Mushrooms and Stumps, rendering them unable to be deployed upon; After this unit's HP drops to 0, it will explode, <$ba.stun>Stunning</> units in a large area and ejecting its pilot, the 'High Priest.'

enemy_1513_dekght.name: Corrupted Knight
enemy_1513_dekght.description: A Sarkaz knight with a broken horn who radiates terror and shows clear signs of excessive drug use. Uses a warhammer in battle. Crushes enemies with terrifying bloodlust. When the Withered Knight falls, takes up the quest and becomes dramatically stronger. Every step he takes spreads corruption.
enemy_1513_dekght.ability: Deals physical damage to its target and four surrounding tiles when attacking. Growth attack deals high physical damage to its target and four surrounding tiles. When the Withered Knight dies, ATK, ASPD, and movement speed are significantly increased.

enemy_1513_dekght_2.name: Withered Knight
enemy_1513_dekght_2.description: A Sarkaz knight with a broken horn who radiates terror and shows clear signs of excessive drug use. Uses a cursed bow in battle. Can shoot multiple targets at once and plant seeds of withering arts. When the Corrupted Knight falls, takes up the quest and becomes dramatically stronger. Knights that are hostile to him will shift to Wither.
enemy_1513_dekght_2.ability: Attacks two targets simultaneously. Fires explosive arrows at three targets, which explode after a short delay, dealing high Arts damage to the target and surrounding four tiles. When the Corrupted Knight dies, ATK, ASPD, and movement speed are significantly increased.

enemy_1514_smephi.name: Mephisto, 'The Singer'
enemy_1514_smephi.description: You seem to recognize the mysterious, mythical beast that has descended from the Sarcophagus. An otherworldly song flows from its sharp beak and floods its surroundings. It seems to devour the will of the Infected around it, including its own. Even if it knows not what it is doing, its song does not cease. It simply wishes to sing.
enemy_1514_smephi.ability: When Activated, heals and strengthens an enemy Host unit; Each time a certain percentage of HP is lost, releases a toxic cloud across the entire battlefield that lasts for 30s and can stack. When HP drops to 0 for the first time, enters a dormant state for a period of time, then gains DEF, RES, and HP regeneration.

enemy_1515_bsnake.name: 'The Deathless Black Snake'
enemy_1515_bsnake.description: A disenchanted Reunion soldier, or a giant manipulating history? A conspirator full of lies, or a nobleman swallowed by tragedy? The truth has been turned to ash, and only an evil god stands in the flames.
enemy_1515_bsnake.ability: Attacks deal True damage and apply [Burning Breath] to the target (Deals increasing True damage each second, but can be <$ba.buffres>resisted</>); Takes greatly reduced damage from targets afflicted by [Burning Breath]; Applies [Burning Breath] to two of your units; Detonates all units on the battlefield afflicted by [Burning Breath], dealing Arts damage to the surrounding four tiles and applying [Burning Breath] to targets hit by this splash effect. When HP drops to 0, releases [Deathless Inferno], dealing massive Arts damage across the battlefield; When Enraged, gains greatly increased HP and ATK and summons [Energy Aggregates] to assist in battle.

enemy_1516_jakill.name: Jesselton Miller
enemy_1516_jakill.description: Jesselton Miller, a killer who infiltrated the prison disguised as a jailer. Very particular in both speech and action, he remains graceful even in the midst of battle.
enemy_1516_jakill.ability: In Jailer form, he has greatly increased RES, uses long-ranged Arts attacks, can <$ba.stun>Stun</> multiple targets, and does not attack Imprisonment Devices; In Killer form, he has greatly increased DEF, uses melee Physical attacks, and ignores a certain amount of the target's DEF; When changing to Killer form, immediately frees all other enemies

enemy_1517_xi.name: 'Free'
enemy_1517_xi.description: A monster drawn by Dusk. It has a commanding presence and chilling arrogance, as though taking a page out of its master's book. 'The virid beasts. Like range on range. Eleven told. In moon, smoke-flow.'
enemy_1517_xi.ability: 'Weft and Warp' deals Arts damage to enemies in the surrounding cross area, changing Hui-Ming attributes within its range; 'Break the Chains': If the shield is not yet broken, deal massive ranged damage; During second phase, attacks twice and additionally unleashes 'Weft and Warp' on farthest target.

enemy_1519_bgball.name: 'Essence of Evolution'
enemy_1519_bgball.description: A madman who should not have stepped upon this world. An oddity that should not have existed in the other world. The union of the two gave birth to this node of 'evolution' that far surpasses the limits of biology. It's existence naturally contradicts all of Terra. It should not live. It must not live.
enemy_1519_bgball.ability: Unable to move; Will evolve after a certain duration or when HP falls below a certain threshold; Periodically creates <Originiutant Excrescence> or <Originiutant Tumor>; Periodically deals a large amount of True damage to all deployed Operators; During [Newborn Form], greatly reduce Physical and Arts damage taken from units to the left; During [Evolution Form], greatly reduce Physical and Arts damage taken from units to the right; During [Perfect Form], massively reduce Physical and Arts damage taken, however lose HP every second

enemy_1520_empgrd.name: 'Emperor's Blade', Pursuer
enemy_1520_empgrd.description: He once ravaged the demons of the Northern Tundra, segregating the outsiders beyond the reach of civilization; His blade shies not from royals nor nobles, safeguarding glory from the dusts of rebellion. Every Royal Guard is as a dominion; the land beneath their feet is all the territory of Ursus.
enemy_1520_empgrd.ability: Whenever a certain percentage of HP is lost, unleashes the permanent terrain effect [Dominion], significantly reducing allied units' ASPD and reducing Physical and Arts damage taken by self when within its effect (Prioritizes targeting the ally unit outside of [Dominion] with the highest damage dealt to self); Casts [Collapsing Fear] which deals Arts damage to nearby units, instantly defeating the target if they are within [Dominion]; The first time HP drops to 0, casts [Collapsing Fear] on the entire battlefield; During his second form, his attacks and skills are more powerful

enemy_1521_dslily.name: Sal Viento Bishop Quintus
enemy_1521_dslily.description: A member of the Church of the Deep who snuck into disaster-ravaged Iberia. He changed the law of the land through his sincere beliefs, in pursuit of the perfect form, yet he was unable to fathom the will of the ocean. Then again, who could?
enemy_1521_dslily.ability: Attacks two targets with the highest DEF simultaneously; [Great Tide] deals Arts damage and <$ba.dt.neural>Nervous Impairment</> to all allied units; [Collapse] deals Physical damage to multiple allied units; [Fragmentation] summons its offspring to entwine themselves around allied units and <$ba.stun>Stun</> them; [Species Outbreak] removes all Life Points when a long time has passed in the battle.

enemy_1522_captan.name: Pancho Salas
enemy_1522_captan.description: Pancho Salas, an old veteran piloting a heavily modified motorboat. Even should his vessel be destroyed, he will never falter before reaching his goal.
enemy_1522_captan.ability: Summons 'Kite' to fight alongside explosive boats; attacks the unit with the highest Max HP with the water cannon and continuously deals Arts damage and <$ba.dt.erosion>Corrosion Damage</>. During the second form, periodically attacks all surrounding units; attacks the unit with the highest DEF with the firearm and reduces the unit's DEF. When defeats a unit or gets defeated, increases the ATK and Movement Speed of all enemy units

enemy_1523_mandra.name: Mandragora
enemy_1523_mandra.description: One of the leaders of the Dublinn forces, a caster who controls stone. Emerging from the darkness of Victoria, she has sworn to repay the humiliation she suffered at the hands of the nobles manyfold.
enemy_1523_mandra.ability: [Stoneshield] Reduces damage taken, temporarily loses effect after being hit by a <@eb.key>Tattered Pillar</>; [Mandragora's Gaze] Targets the unit with the highest ATK within range, dealing Arts damage and reducing their ASPD. If the target is retreated or defeated, destroy the tile the unit was on; In her second form, [Stoneshield] also grants <$ba.float>Low-Altitude Hovering</>, and Mandragora becomes able to knock down <@eb.key>Tattered Pillars</>

enemy_1524_bldkgt.name: The Blood Knight Dikaiopolis
enemy_1524_bldkgt.description: The Blood Knight, Dikaiopolis. The originator of Kazimierz's Infected Knight program, the hero of the Grand Knight Territory's Infected, and an idol to countless children. What exactly did the 'hero' give up to obtain the peace we know today?
enemy_1524_bldkgt.ability: Reduce damage taken, however this effect is ineffective against the unit blocking self; 'Exsanguination': Stun the target and deal Arts damage every second; After the HP of his first form drops to 0, enters 'Resurrection Stance'. During this period, the Blood Knight is invulnerable and continuously summons Bloodblades, and enters the second form after some time. If the Blood Knight's HP is restored to its maximum while in 'Resurrection Stance', he will return to his first form; During his second form, he has increased ATK, uses ranged attacks, and continuously summons Bloodblades.

enemy_1525_blkswb.name: Degenbrecher
enemy_1525_blkswb.description: Three-time champion of the Kazimierz Major, a defective Leithanian unable to use Arts, a natural-born warrior—The Black Knight.
enemy_1525_blkswb.ability: Immune to <$ba.frozen>Frozen</> and gains <$ba.buffres>status resistance</>; ATK increases during snowfall and, when blocked, attacks against the blocker ignore a certain amount of DEF; [Swift Slayer] When blocked, bypasses the target and deals Physical damage to units along the path; [Brutalizing Blizzard] Deals Physical damage to units in the surrounding area; During her second form, gain <$ba.invisible>Invisibility</>, attacks ignore more DEF and deal damage twice, [Momentum Murder] Whenever 25% HP is lost, clears the SP of all allied units in range and prevent the targets from attacking or healing for some time.

enemy_1526_sfsui.name: 'Sui-Xiang'
enemy_1526_sfsui.description: The shadow of the bestial Sui, towering and venerable. It casts its lazy gaze upon the mortal realm, and in the blink of an eye a thousand years have come and gone. With the millennium passing like a dream, it is uncertain whether it is feeling anger or bitterness.
enemy_1526_sfsui.ability: Reduces damage taken from above and below; When defeated during its Stage 1 or 2 form, after a period of time, the unit takes its next form and reappears a certain distance to the right; [Faraway Mountains' Thunderclap] Deals continuous Arts damage to units within cross areas around three ranged units; [Heavensfall] Deals Physical damage twice to melee units and additionally inflicts continuous Arts damage that slowly increases over time (can be <$ba.buffres>resisted</>); [Omnidirectional Breath] Inflicts continuous damage to a large area to the right and renders the tiles no longer available for deployment; Operators in the left side of the target area can reduce damage taken by allied units to the right and mitigate damage to the tiles.

enemy_1527_martyr.name: Andoain, the 'Martyr'
enemy_1527_martyr.description: A Sankta who made an enemy of Laterano for the sake of asking a question. A Pathfinder who tread the path of peril for the sake of receiving an answer. He feels neither wrath nor sorrow. He neither curses God, nor beseeches man. Andoain only follows his own path, wherever it may end.
enemy_1527_martyr.ability: Cannot be blocked. While holding Ammo, this unit gains increased ATK, and attacks will cause Ammo to bounce to a nearby target, up to a maximum of <@eb.key>5</> bounces, dealing additional damage to 'Gelato Stops'. Ammo capacity: <@eb.key>5</>; After losing a certain percentage of HP, creates a permanent field effect, 'Light Unto Sufferers'. Enemies standing on 'Light Unto Sufferers' take reduced Physical and Arts Damage and gain 50% Physical and Arts Dodge. After being defeated once, enters his Second Form, gaining increased ATK and periodically using 'Ashes to Ashes, Dust to Dust': Andoain stops attacking and scans the battlefield from left to right, locking onto at most 5 targets before dealing massive Physical Damage to them and fully replenishing his Ammo.

enemy_1528_manfri.name: Manfred
enemy_1528_manfri.description: A young Sarkaz general, member of the Military Commission of Kazdel. After enlisting a large number of mercenaries in Londinium, he has assembled and trained a brand new type of fighting force. His Arts Unit 'Teekaz's Root' was bestowed upon him by Theresis, the Regent of Kazdel, who also taught him the swordsmanship he now employs.
enemy_1528_manfri.ability: Uses his floating cannon to inflict Arts damage; Upon firing, floating cannon will charge up Londinium Secondary Defense Artillery. [Focus] Continuously gains ASPD when attacking the same target (this effect is capped), rapidly decaying when switching targets or not attacking for a few seconds; [Military Training] Has high Physical and Arts dodge, but after being bombarded by the City Defense Artillery, temporarily loses this dodge effect and is stunned for a few seconds; [From Withered Trunk, New Branches] When defeated for the first time, randomly attacks all targets on the battlefield with his floating cannon, greatly accelerating the charge rate of Londinium Secondary Defense Artillery; In his second form, draws his sword alongside his floating cannon to perform simultaneous Physical and Arts attacks.

enemy_1529_dsdevr.name: The Endspeaker, Will of We Many
enemy_1529_dsdevr.description: The tiny Seaborn that haunted the mighty Stultifera, the blood of its parents once strewn across the ocean's waters. The revelation reaches not the ears of the children, their kind's destiny quietly continuing to flow.
enemy_1529_dsdevr.ability: When defeated, disappears for a short time before evolving into its next form, gaining the following effects in turn: Gains increased DEF/Gains increased Movement Speed/Gains increased ATK and Lifesteal; [Consume] Consumes the Remains of its Seaborn kin, gaining their corresponding Directed Evolution ability in the next evolutionary phase, while also instantly defeating any Operators near the Remains and preventing them from being redeployed for a period of time.

enemy_1530_white.name: Kreide, 'Worldly Remains'
enemy_1530_white.description: Kreide's form, covered in layers of Originium, calls forth only fear in Leithanien. He stopped the Voice of Terra from consuming others, yet he himself was consumed in turn. He tried to save everyone present, yet there remains only one way to save him.
enemy_1530_white.ability: Attacks deal <@eb.key>splash</> damage. When blocked, attacks inflict <$ba.stun>Stun</>; [The Final Rest] Starts with increased DEF and RES; After being defeated the first time, temporarily changes to an allied unit, then loses the increased DEF and RES, and increases ATK and skill power instead; [Resonance Overload] Causes Realigned Flux to deal continuous damage; [Lamentation of Nothingness] Attacks all targets on the field in order and loses a large amount of HP. When in Realigned Flux, <@eb.key>ASPD is reduced</>

enemy_1531_bbrain.name: “唤醒”
enemy_1531_bbrain.description: 多萝西亲手制造的“梦境”，在这里，人们不必再忍受跋涉之苦。科技无法做到的事情，爱与希望可以。
enemy_1531_bbrain.ability: 无法移动；每隔一段时间将自己转移至指定地块并施放【破碎愿景】，对场上所有单位造成一次巨大物理伤害，该伤害将由所有友方单位平均分摊；每隔一段时间，向左右两个方向施放【旅程】，对首个击中的单位造成物理伤害；“唤醒”受到伤害时，将50%的伤害转移给场上其他多萝西实验体；第二形态下攻击力提升，立刻激活场上所有R系列动力装甲，【破碎愿景】还能使处于高台的单位<$ba.stun>晕眩</>并且“唤醒”会向周围4个方向施放【旅程】。

enemy_1532_minima.name: 'Materialist Antagonizer'
enemy_1532_minima.description: Construction machinery attempting to protect Stitch Canvas, under the mistaken impression that he is about to be attacked. Before explaining what's actually going on, let's settle things with a test of strength first.
enemy_1532_minima.ability: While on the battlefield, increases the strength of all [Machina] enemies; attacks will deploy small drones that deal continuous Arts damage to the target for a period of time, prioritizing targets that are not already locked onto by these drones; periodically refreshes a shield that can resist Physical and Arts damage, and grants <$ba.invisible>Invisibility</> to other enemies within attack range as long as this shield holds; periodically locks on to the friendly unit with the <@eb.key>greatest number of units around it</> and continuously deals Arts damage in an area around that unit; periodically locks on to the friendly unit with the <@eb.key>fewest number of units around it</> and continuously inflicts <$ba.stun>Stun</> in an area around that unit; when HP drops to 0, Stitch will appear and be <$ba.stun>Stunned</> for a period of time

enemy_1533_stmkgt.name: “最后的蒸汽骑士”
enemy_1533_stmkgt.description: 蒸汽骑士是维多利亚的荣耀，代表着维多利亚的最强战力和授予士兵的最高荣誉。最后一位蒸汽骑士于尘封的废墟中站起，为守护他心中的维多利亚而发起冲锋。
enemy_1533_stmkgt.ability: 出场时攻击和移动速度降低，释放【蒸汽增压】后解除；【蒸汽增压】攻击和移动速度提升，且免疫控制，结束时眩晕；【怒守】蓄力攻击，造成更高的三次伤害；【誓死】每损失一定生命值后起飞，锁定我方<@eb.key>生命上限最高</>的单位，对其周围<@eb.key>生命比例最高</>的单位造成多次法术伤害；第二形态下防御和法术抗性降低，永久处于【蒸汽增压】，【誓死】额外锁定一个目标。

enemy_1535_wlfmster.name: 扎罗，“狼之主”
enemy_1535_wlfmster.description: 狼之主，自荒野中诞生，却将目光投向人世。自视甚高，机关算尽，然功亏一篑，满盘皆输。如今，该有人承受他的怒火了。
enemy_1535_wlfmster.ability: 使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>逐渐增加；受到伤害降低；【溶血骇惧】使三名我方单位被恐惧吞噬，不可主动撤退，攻速大幅降低，并逐渐加速失去生命值；受影响单位在“狼之主”损失一定比例生命时，会恢复正常；第一形态生命值降为0后，获得【远古威慑】，周围我方单位降低攻击速度，并缓慢回复生命值。第二形态下，不再拥有减伤，可被晕眩，且不再释放【溶血骇惧】。攻击变为远程二连击，且攻击力提升。每隔一段时间释放，【狂暴怒嗥】，使<@eb.key>“血债账款”</>快速上升

enemy_1536_ncrmcr.name: “领袖”
enemy_1536_ncrmcr.description: 深池的“领袖”，焚烧生命的德拉克，一个令人恐惧的影子。不要被她困住。
enemy_1536_ncrmcr.attackType: 近战 远程 法术
enemy_1536_ncrmcr.ability: 【新生】在场时，部分敌人被击倒后会变为“余烬”继续作战；【主宰】对一名目标释放<@eb.key>焦竭之火</>，使其无法攻击、释放技能，<@eb.key>焦竭之火</>消逝或附着目标撤退时对十字范围内所有我方单位造成法术伤害与<$ba.dt.burning>灼燃损伤</>；【予取予夺】献祭至多5名“逐火战士”，并根据献祭数获得相当于自身最大生命值一定比例的物理/法术护盾，护盾持续一段时间。第二形态下攻击力提升，立即点燃场上所有芦苇丛，近战攻击造成两次攻击力一定比例的伤害，远程攻击和【主宰】可以额外选择一个目标

enemy_1538_ymmons.name: “睚”
enemy_1538_ymmons.description: 巨兽“睚”的代理人。据司岁台古卷记载，千年前炎国所围猎的巨兽之一“睚”，拥有“裁错春秋”的神奇能力。伤口永难愈合，祂舔舐着屈辱、愤怒与不解......祂回到了熟悉的炎土。
enemy_1538_ymmons.attackType: 近战 远程 法术
enemy_1538_ymmons.ability: 在经过的地块生成“无念之冬”，【“无念之冬”】持续召唤敌人；【春生】被阻挡时召唤蜃景，蜃景<$ba.float>近地悬浮</>、在经过的地块生成“无念之冬”，一段时间后未被击败则“睚”传送到蜃景的位置。第一形态生命值降为0后，获得【秋荣】、【裁剪春秋】、【天地如自】，第二形态下攻击范围扩大，攻击变为远程攻击，获得<$ba.float>近地悬浮</>。【秋荣】在场上召唤妄境，妄境在经过的地块生成“无念之冬”，拥有和“睚”相似的能力。“睚”被击败时，妄境死亡；妄境死亡时，“睚”丢失部分最大生命值；【裁剪春秋】“睚”和妄境对自身周围单位造成一次范围伤害，随后交换位置和行进路线；【天地如自】“睚”和妄境对自身周围单位造成一次范围伤害。

enemy_1538_ymmons_2.name: 蜃景
enemy_1538_ymmons_2.attackType: 近战 远程 法术

enemy_1538_ymmons_3.name: 妄境
enemy_1538_ymmons_3.attackType: 近战 远程 法术

enemy_2003_rockman.name: Lost Colossus
enemy_2003_rockman.description: An experimental creation of a certain caster from the Spires of Leithanien. This colossus was originally made to be a 'servant,' but the old Spire caster forgot to tell him who he should serve...
enemy_2003_rockman.ability: Drains 2 Objective HP when entering the Objective Point; Can throw a rock that inflicts a very long <$ba.stun>Stun</> (will not target a unit that is already <$ba.stun>Stunned</>).

enemy_2004_balloon.name: Jetman
enemy_2004_balloon.description: One of the dessert-time jokes among Columbians involves a strange man who calls himself a 'Master Thief,' puttering around with a self-made jetpack. The most valuable thing he's stolen is a single burdenbeast. However, the fact that he made his own jetpack might mean that he really is a master.
enemy_2004_balloon.ability: Drains 5 Objective HP when entering the Objective Point; When blocked, this unit will take off for a period of time (this effect has a cooldown period).

enemy_2005_axetro.name: 'Forsaken One'
enemy_2005_axetro.description: 'The rescuers found a security guard who had been heavily corroded by Originium... already turned into a terrifying monster... carnage everywhere... countless casualties... whereabouts unknown.' —Rim Billiton mining record
